programme.title: NYC Freestyle
programme.desc: Music, art, and community: the elements of hip-hop culture come together on a 'freestyled' night in New York. Baxter and Amber are a couple in New York City out on the town without a plan. They freestyle their way through a night filled with all the elements of the hip-hop scene — music, art, and community — and show the upside of being up for anything.

programme.title: BMX Nigeria
programme.sub-title: A ray of light and radness
programme.desc: This is the inspiring story of two pioneers from the nascent BMX scene in Lagos, Nigeria. This is the inspiring story of two pioneers from the nascent BMX scene in Lagos, Nigeria. Get to know how they got their start in riding and find out how the small crew have forged a whole new frontier in BMX.

programme.title: Kings of Content
programme.sub-title: Meet the superstars of viral video
programme.desc: Go inside the world of video creation and meet the content mavericks set to become the next viral sensation. Meet the stars of online content and discover what it takes to create a global viral sensation. From funny animals to far-out stunts, fashion vlogs to gaming shows, these are the creators who’ve taken over everyone’s feed.

programme.title: Tapati Rapa Nui
programme.desc: Descendants of Easter Island's native tribes hold an ancient competition of strength, endurance, and bravery. Each year descendants of the ancient Easter Island native tribes continue the proud tradition of the Tapati Rapa Nui, a competition of strength, endurance, and bravery. Winning garners only pride, but the dangers in the challenges are very real.

programme.title: The Outer Reaches of 8-Bit
programme.desc: Discover how Konami and Sunsoft's bold musical choices pushed Japanese video game music forward. Thanks to advanced technologies during Japan's 'Bubble Era', companies like Konami and Sunsoft were able to push video game music to the next level by creating thicker sounds and creatively combining different musical genres.

programme.title: Sharing the Sky
programme.desc: Multi-discipline pilot Andy Hediger was born to fly, but a near-fatal crash almost clipped his wings forever. Multi-discipline aerobatic pilot and Red Bull Aerobatic Team member Andy Hediger was born to fly. But a near-fatal crash means that even walking again may be a miracle. Now Andy must fight his way back to health if he hopes to return to the sky.

programme.title: Test driving before Goodwood
programme.desc: 'Mad' Mike Whiddett's Lamborghini Huracán is ready for its big reveal at the Goodwood Festival of Speed. 'Mad' Mike Whiddett's Lamborghini Huracán is finally ready for its big reveal at the Goodwood Festival of Speed, but first he's got to make sure it doesn't get flattened by Kamaz's huge Dakar truck.

programme.title: Living Forever
programme.desc: American rapper GZA is on a quest to understand the age-old human desire to live forever. In his quest to understand the human desire to live forever, American rapper GZA finds out how bodies are stored in Arizona, visits a California lab studying the immortal hydra, and goes to Vermont’s transhumanist Terasem Foundation.

programme.title: Séan Garnier vs The World
programme.sub-title: From the streets to the stage to the top
programme.desc: Freestyle football has been Séan Garnier’s ticket to the world, but success never comes without sacrifice. From the streets to the pinnacle of freestyle success, Séan’s Garnier’s prodigal journey has been one of self-discovery through football.

programme.title: Asia Rising
programme.desc: Seen through the eyes of a diverse group, we take a look at the fast-paced success of Asian hip-hop. With the help of record label 88rising, we look at six different artists from six different backgrounds, all within Asia, as they share their thoughts on the recent rise of hip-hop in the region.

programme.title: Mountain Biking Will Ruin Your Life
programme.desc: Mountain biking can be addicting, and for both pros and amateurs there’s no better fix than Whistler, Canada. For those who can't break into the pro ranks, travelling with the Enduro World Series as a photographer might be the next best thing. And for mountain bikers of all sorts, there’s no better place to go than Whistler, Canada.

programme.title: Method Movie 3
programme.desc: True to the core. Storied snowboard publication Method Magazine returns with the final film of the Method Movie triad, a globetrotting collection of insane snowboarding and good times that, once again, stays a bit weirder than the rest.

programme.title: Cooking at the Catalan Grand Prix
programme.desc: Host Vanessa Guerra is in Barcelona for Catalan GP, chatting with drivers on the track and in the kitchen. In Barcelona for the Catalan GP Vanessa Guerra challenges Pol Espargaró and Johann Zarco to a cooking challenge, then heads to the track to chat with drivers, and Marc Márquez show us his new livery.

programme.title: The Resilient
programme.desc: The chasing of a dream is fraught with failure, but those who achieve greatness approach failure differently. Those who can weather the many defeats on the road to success are the ones who ultimately achieve their dreams. Craig Venter, the man who mapped the human genome, and skateboard pioneer Stacy Peralta show how they persisted in the face of failure.

programme.title: Surfers' Blood
programme.desc: A film by Patrick Trefz. Renowned surf photographer and filmmaker Patrick Trefz explores the essence of the sport he loves by profiling those who inspire him. From Basque Country, Spain, to Silicon Valley, USA, these unique people are united by a deep connection to the sea.

programme.title: Tim Don
programme.desc: The Man with the Halo. While cycling in Kona, Hawaii as part of his final prep for IRONMAN, Tim Don was hit by a truck. Scans showed Tim had broken his neck. It was the end of Tim’s hopes of competing at the World Championship, but thankfully it was not the end of Tim.
